{
  "message": "test(conformance): dataframe groupby ngroup packet (FP-P2D-112)\n\nAdds conformance coverage for `DataFrame.groupby().ngroup()` \u2014\npandas's group-ordinal helper that assigns a dense integer label per\ngroup (preserving the groupby iteration order). Pairs with the\nearlier kurtosis / skew / sem / ohlc groupby packets already\nregistered.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs\n  * New `#[test] packet_filter_runs_dataframe_groupby_ngroup_packet`:\n    calls `run_packet_by_id(&cfg, \"FP-P2D-112\",\n    OracleMode::FixtureExpected)` and asserts:\n      - `report.packet_id == Some(\"FP-P2D-112\")`\n      - `report.fixture_count >= 3` (three fixtures registered in\n        the next bullet)\n      - `report.is_green()` \u2014 all fixtures match the oracle bytes.\n\ncrates/fp-conformance/fixtures/packets/\n  * New fixtures in the standard FP-P2D packet shape:\n      - fp_p2d_112_dataframe_groupby_ngroup_basic_strict.json\n        Strict-mode basic case: 6-row DataFrame grouped on one\n        column; expected output is the [0, 0, 1, 1, 2, 2]\n        ordinal Series.\n      - fp_p2d_112_dataframe_groupby_ngroup_multi_group_hardened.json\n        Hardened-mode case with three groups interleaved and a\n        NaN-key row; exercises NaN handling.\n      - fp_p2d_112_dataframe_groupby_ngroup_single_group_strict.json\n        Edge case: everyone in one group, so ngroup = [0, 0, 0, \u2026].\n        Catches implementations that start labels at 1.\n\nNo runtime-code change.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>",
